	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f104920549766231><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj>Soloed the Book of Souls</span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=61546><span id=Scholar>Slipskin</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>768 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Apr 1st 9:34 AM 2003</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.62]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I succesfully completed the Book of Souls run in Plane of Hate last night.&nbsp;&nbsp;Got a wizzie friend to port me up. Got the book and gated with a Thurgadin Gate potion.  Elapsed time - 27 minutes.<br><br>One note to those of you planning your own epic run - only the scorn banshees and loathing liches can see thru sneak/hide.  Even then they have small aggro radii.  I had liches looking right at me at about throwing axe range and caught no aggro.  They con'd &quot;scowling&quot; but did not attack. I didn't try to get any closer.  I walked right over several revnants, a couple of ire ghasts and a cleric of Innoruk with no trouble at all. They all con'd indifferent as long as I kept hide/sneak up.<br><br>Be careful. When you pick up the book it will break hide (but not sneak).  So rehide as soon as you grab the book.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
